see, the rates were cheaper and so on you see and the rents were cheaper. And - most of them seemed to have congregate in Bridgford. And it got that feeling amongst the working class people in these lower - class districts - that - these Bridgford people 
h
ad an idea that they were something - better. See I give you an instance in - in my survey, where this fellow that - this manager that I worked under at Morley's - he - he got an idea he was something big because he could have a bath every morning and I c
