s a name they got because they thought they were something superior. You see. I mean there's - there's - there's people that I worked for when I was a lad, I used to have to go to Bridgford - to fetch his dinner on a Saturday and walk, a matter of two mil
e
 or more, and bring his dinner back. And that woman, although she was cooking - at the time I got there for his dinner, she wouldn't offer you a cake or a tart. Oh no. Because you were something - under them. You see. Oh no, they wouldn't do that, they we
re - they were - I should call them a very mean lot actually.
\par 
